  "text": "is decreasing in θ. So it either crosses 0 once or remains positive till θ = 1. Thus we know either M is always increasing, or first increases to a maximum and then decreases. The result slightly differs from the optimal damages case because we cannot let θ go to infinity as . So at full injunction, the society's marginal benefit of protection may still be positive. [CITATION_1] It is not hard to verify that the first order derivative is positive at θ = 0, so θ = 0 is never optimal.",
